metadata.name: Fabrics
metadata.description:
Fabric. A collection of swatches. 

This is a project of stacked PNGs producing fabric swatches. Some are almost plaids, others are more batik, while others are more of a "magic eye" or optical illusion look. 

The PNGs were generated using VBA and conditional formatting in MS Excel, then copy/pasted as an image into MS PowerPoint, and occasionally further manipulated in different image editors including MS Paint. Images were batch resized to match each other at 1125x1125.

There are a lot of options for this collection. The layers and total number of options per (included "none" layers):
- Base
    - 42
- Flecking 
    - 18
- Broad
    - 50
- Underpin
    - 43
- Warp
    - 21
- Weft
    - 26
- Overpins
    - 43
- Mask
    - 21
- Texture
    - 14


There is a slight potential to mint the "imaginary fabric", one which is comprised of only "none" layers. That is the best of the bunch, because it is only limited by your imagination. Consider it the legendary.

There should be an interplay between the coded elements of each individual PNG and the overall stack. The randomness of coded layers stacked with other, dissimilar (base) coded layers generates interesting, and at times, colorful patterns that don't have a singular, obvious, overarching algo.

Hope you enjoy! 

Stacking achieved using PureSpider's pfp code https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

License CC BY-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Σ 360 Points of View
metadata.description:
What we see is normally a 2d projection from a 3d world. 
This is the representation of how things can be absorbed from our own perspective
and how important is to go all the way around, to move from our point of view.

Use the mouse to change your perspective. 
Right click for moving the orbit and wheel for getting away or closer.

Choose your perspective the token will be minted from your own point of view.

  Hope you enjoy it
 Gonz.-

metadata.name: FAUVE
metadata.description:
Fauve is legion. Fauve is crowd. Fauve is pressure.

Fauve is a collection open for interpretation. It explores the feeling of gathering many entities in a tight space. These circle entities seem to be looking straight back at you, waiting for something to happen.
If these entites were humans, what do you think they would feel in this moment?
What do you feel when you look at them?

metadata.name: Spiraling
metadata.description:
Look inside of you. What do you feel? What do you say to people when they ask "How's it going?"

There are 3 variations for Spiraling. I call them phases. 

Phase 1 is the most common and has a 70% chance of occurring. This phase is typically fuzzy on the inside and slightly unstable on the outside. 

Phase 2 has a 20% chance of occurring. This phase is the most unstable. 

Phase 3 is the one shown in the preview and has a 10% chance of occurring. It is typically very zen on the inside, and slightly unstable on the outside. 

Each token generates a series of 180 circles using both random values and a noise map based on the base hash. 

---

This is a deterministic version of the phase loop experiments on cliqu.art for you to collect! Each one is unique and can't be generated from the experiments.

metadata.name: Los Generators - Enter The Machine
metadata.description:
From Spain we present our FxHash Genesis, a layered png generative artwork:

Los Generators - Enter The Machine
"100 years ago, a family of inventors trying to break into the metaverse, its 2022 and they made it."

The post-folk band is a rare gem, working tirelessly to get this album to web3, set like clockwork the family of Spanish musician-inventors ensures that their effort was not in vain.

Enter The Machine is a concept album, chronicling the inventiveness of an isolated family, creating trinkets and instruments that would make it possible for their album to be encrypted in 1922 and only surface in 2022, where its unique content can be enjoyed.

Los Generators invite you to discover their universe, presented through several randomized album covers, with different graphics and characters, with more than 900 combination possibilities.

Can you imagine their music?

The code part was created using the P5 library to make the combinations between the ready-made layers and manipulate the pixels, placing the layers overlay on a canvas in the html and creating a noise filter using the 'loadPixel()' function.
A simple function was made to save the canvas when pressing the 'P' key, saving a png in 1000x1000p resolution.

Album cover condition: various.
1000x1000 pixels, PNG, 32 bit.
Metabandz and nt_worm, 2022.

Metabandz is a label releasing album cover nft's for fictional music bands.

metadata.name: Unknown Squigl
metadata.description:
Squigls flowing through the Tezos Blockchain.

Unknown Squigl is created with four different themes: 

Monochrome - Squigls with light shade of random hue 
Complementary - Strokes with complementarish color calculated from background hue
Ukraine - 211° for yellow and 50° for the blue
Grayscale - Random background shade of gray and an opposite shade of gray for the strokes

And a few different versions for offsetting the strokes.

The pixelDensity can be changed with pressing keys 1,2,4 or 8. (8 can be slow!)
Image can be downloaded in live view with pressing key 's'.

Created with P5JS.

hic et squigl / 2022

metadata.name: Fx(Interfaces)
metadata.description:
WGMInterfaces said goodbye to the NFT space a day ago. 

Being an absolute fan of their work, sometimes, taking time for yourself is needed in this space and I know it’s not an easy decision for them. I had so much love for their philosophy and fun at designing this derivative PFP project for the FxHash family as a tribute to the team at WAGMInterfaces.

While they return, let's cherish the derivative in the meantime. 

Behance: www.behance.net/gallery/138404877/Interfaces-WAGMI-Inspired

metadata.name: Organicon, variation I
metadata.description:
Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
512 unique generators creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation I is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. Warning: the preview thumbnail is a pale shadow of live view.

Interface: a first mouse click clears the screen, creates an new iteration and enables active mode. In active mode each iteration remains on screen for a limited amount of time before being replaced by the next. A second mouse click disables active mode. In active mode a small dot is displayed in the lower right corner. '+' and '-' zoom in and out.

metadata.name: Tree Skyness
metadata.description:
Tree Skyness

Crown shyness occurs when the tops of fully grown trees avoid touching each other, forming gaps in the canopy. This piece simulates that phenomena and plays with celestial object avoidance. Features include four seasons, time of day, up to 12 trees, and many special options. HD rendering can be enabled for 8192x8192 resolution. 10% of primary sales will be donated to the fxhash Ukraine fund.

Click to randomize with the same settings.

By Frank Force @KilledByAPixel
Made with Vanilla JavaScript

Controls
1 = Save a 2048x2048 png (or right click save)
2 = Toggle HD (may not work in some environments)
3 = Toggle noise (disable for clearer image)

metadata.name: monopole
metadata.description:
Physics is, above all, beautiful.

Inspired by all the things I find beautiful in physics, and the nostalgia I feel for my undergraduate days of learning about the universe. I sought here to explore what can be created with simple graphics showing simple physical systems. 

The vector field shown is the field from a collection of monopoles, such as electrons and positrons or hypothetical magnetic monopoles.

The papers and inks available are those I have on my desk.

A 2400x2400 download of the image can be generated by pressing UP, but this will take several minutes. An SVG download can be made by pressing DOWN and is suitable for plotting (or laser cutting).

metadata.name: 生成畫荷
metadata.description:
It ain't hard to tell, code compiles, and then art reveals.

「天一生水，地六成之；地二生火，天七成之；天三生木，地八成之；地四生金，天九成之；天五生土，地十成之。天生地成，而行鬼神。」— 河圖

Heaven gens, earth erates, the acts of demons and gods, indefinitely, generate. 

荷花一現，河圖不見，生花成畫，心幸有憐。

I see that lotus, but this code does not render it. Flowers are generative, art is generative, and we feel. 

「自抒胸意，不襲前人；無人無我，無古無今」— 張大千七十七歲作

There is no I nor they, past or present. — Zhang Da Qian~1976

「墨落一時手不住，任譏老子做狂徒。」— 張大千八十四歲作

Oops! ink fell out of my hand. But, I, got it.  — Zhang Da Qian~1983

“We see things in things, 
then create and drop,
copyminters only look at commits, 
on github. 
Though they need not to peek,
my gen art’s free, to see, 
stuff on my mind, 
do not like, to be locked, in a file, 
it ain’t hard to smell.” — Zhang Da Qian x Nas x Jimi Wen

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Robosort
metadata.description:
Sorting pixels isn't the preferred pastime for most humans. This state-of-the-art algorithm helps automatically sort pixels to free humans for more important tasks...such as achieving inbox zero or binge watching the latest Netflix series.

If you prefer to manually sort pixels, check out Unsorted. https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/10029

- 't' changes colors
- 'p' saves jpg of the current screen
- There are 10 difficulty levels
- The algorithm stops after the move count is reached

- 'p' saves jpg of the current screen
- There are 10 difficulty levels
- The algorithm stops after the move count is reached

metadata.name: BROKEN SCORE SYNTH
metadata.description:
Broken Score Synth is a generative graphics / animation with a single voice sound synthesis.

-- Click on the screen to enable / disable playing and the sound.

-- Hover your mouse over the notes to play.

-- Press numbers 1 to 4 to change the line density (and note size).

-- Press "E" for new Broken Score Synth (with the same line density)

-- Press "Q" to raise the pitch by one octave.

-- Press "W" to decrease the pitch by one octave.

-- Press "L" to change score lines orientation (horizontal / vertical)

-- Press "F" to change score lines fill (filled / no fill)

-- Press "B" to change background color.

-- Press "S" in live mode to save png.


The default octave is set to 4

The possible range of notes is from C0 to H9.

Notes (C, D, E, F, G, A, H) and key signatures (b, #) are randomly assigned.

In the Console view, you can keep track of the notes that are currently playing.
If the notes are close or overlapping, you can hear cracking sounds.
(Larger speakers are recommended for listening to low frequencies)

On the lines with less density, notes oscillate and play faster, and on denser lines they play slower.

This work is designed to fill the entire window.

made with p5.js and p5.sound.js

metadata.name: radium
metadata.description:
Simulating the idea  about if the human eye could get able to see the radiation frequencies.

"radium" is trying to bring the wondering of if its would be possible naturarely, how it would be if we see ultraviolet lights, radio waves and things like that, as some other earth creatures...

The variations is on some patterns that goes through looking like an the edge of a black hole, planet rings, and in some times even a landscape...

The soul of "radium" is the colormaps that are set to randomize the time its inserting new colors, the form of paint, intensity, the diffusion of grainy noise and the pattern of growth to simulate the frequencies emanation.
 A  sequential pulse growing or a rectroative pulse that grows  after it goes and came back in the opposite direction.




this is a work in p5.js

Omar Lobato Neto, 28/08/2022
Pompéu, Minas Gerais.

metadata.name: ascii DUN-GEN
metadata.description:
This token(DUNgeon GENerator) gives the user the ability to generate any of my maps with a user input size. Each map is a square and runs the computations to build the maps like in my previous works. The best part is the export option. In Live mode, hit 's' to generate a txt file of the map in ascii. This file holds everything you need to import these maps into your own works. Read it line by line and you'll have a randomly generated map in your project.

DUNGEON, ARENA, SWAMP, COURTYARD, CAVE and FOREST. Colors added just for visuals.

Dungeon uses a room placement algorithm of my own and then an implementation of A* to connect each room. The A* only runs orthogonally. Cave is random walk but with some extras to make it more cave like.

Create your own RogueLike!

NOTE: The numerical input accepts only numbers but I haven't tested all the bounds. I usually stop around 200 and...don't do negatives.

metadata.name: WaveFlow 国产波动系列

The wave series works adopt the generation algorithm to generate regular wave effects through the combination brushes of different images, which has an impact on people's vision. It is a new attempt of domestic generation art, hoping to bring more inspiration to more collectors and artists.

波动系列作品采用生成算法，通过不同图像的组合画笔，生成有规则的波动的效果，给人的视觉带来冲击，是国产生成艺术的新尝试，希望给更过的藏家和艺术家带来更多灵感。

metadata.name: Exiles
metadata.description:
Terrans who are not as advanced as the other races in the galaxy, didn't even dream of getting into contact with alien races, let alone going out to the space. They weren't as advanced in technology as Vendians, so when the war broke, they got defeated by Vendians, who didn't even break a sweat. That was alone a reason for humans to feel angry against the aliens. But in addition to that, their nobles and high society made a deal with Vendians, which included a massive portion of the population becoming slaves in exchange of the nobles going out to colonies in the space. They became slaves to Vendians with people from other planets that Vendians have conquered. Because of that, all the people on earth had a common goal. To create a rebellion so big, that even their "mighty masters" will tremble before.


This project is our beginning. For more information:
twitter.com/PixeliusArt
https://twitter.com/AdAstraTheGame
discord.gg/gYQDu3aH5y
metadata.childrenDescription: They called it Exodus. Because they wanted to remember their slavement was nothing but temporary. And they wanted every person from every race wanted to remember that. It didn't matter which race they belonged to. In Exodus, everyone was equal. They just wanted everyone to remember that, one day, every race was going to take their home planet back. They just had to stick together as a community, as a rebellion, as one.
